news.title: Repco Home Finance invites applications for MD, CEO post
news.para: ​Promoted by Repco Bank, Repco Home Finance has invited candidates with minimum qualification of a postgraduate degree in any subject from a UGC recognised university on a full-time basis.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji in talks to raise up to $375 million via Dubai property sale
news.para: ​​Shapoorji Pallonji International (SPINT) is the global arm of Shapoorji Pallonji Engineering & Construction (SP E&C) for its construction operations outside of India. SPINT has successfully built hundreds of diversified landmark structures worldwide in various segments, including residential, commercial, industrial, healthcare, hospitality, educational and stadiums.

news.title: ED seizes Indian, foreign currencies, documents of investment in IREO raids
news.para: According to the Enforcement Directorate (ED), the raids covered "business premises of IREO Pvt. Ltd, IDM Reality Pvt. Ltd, Madeira Conbuild Pvt. Ltd, Global Estate and others."

news.title: Some bondholders of China's Kaisa Group tap adviser to help recover dues: Source
news.para: Kaisa, which has the most offshore debt of any Chinese developer after China Evergrande Group, has not paid coupons totalling over $59 million due on Nov. 11 and 12, with 30-day grace periods for both.

news.title: UK to make electric car charging points compulsory in new buildings
news.para: Prime Minister Boris Johnson told business leaders that he will legislate to compel charging points in new homes, supermarkets and workplaces in England, as part of his carbon-slashing plans.

news.title: NoBroker raises $210 million in Series E funding round
news.para: With this funding NoBroker has now become an  unicorn. This brings the total funding raised by NoBroker to USD $361 million till date.

news.title: MHADA inks pact with Chadha Developers for affordable housing township near Mumbai
news.para: More than 1,000 applicants have already been selected for the allotment through a lottery draw in the last two lots since its launch in September 2021. A lottery for around 3,000 flats will be closing on December 25, while the draw date is January 1.

news.title: Rail ministry told to explain 'contradictory stand' on rehabilitation policy
news.para: The bench was hearing the plea against an order passed by the Gujarat HC, directing eviction of over 10,000 slum dwellers living near railway lines in Surat.

news.title: More families to be displaced by Noida airport's second phase, says report
news.para: Explaining why more families would need to be displaced, an official pointed out that many houses and other such structures had come up on the plots over the past couple of years.

news.title: Urban development bodies set up for Coimbatore, Tirupur
news.para: The announcement to create a separate body for the fast-growing districts were made in the revised budget speech on August 8.

news.title: Awfis leases 64,000 sq ft space to WayCool Foods in Bengaluru & Chennai
news.para: The deal was facilitated by CBRE South Asia. Awfis plans to reach 100 centres before the end of 2021.

news.title: Ingka Centres to invest Rs 3,500 crore to build mixed-use development in Gurugram
news.para: Ingka Centres 52nd meeting place will be developed under the new Livat brand. Construction will start in early 2022 and is expected to generate more than 2,500 jobs.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: SIA report recommends rehabilitation of people
news.para: The study by the institute of rural development has recommended rehabilitation of people who will be evicted from Panathura, Koonamthuruthu and Kilayantemudumbu. As much as 54.105 ares of land belonging to 16 individuals will be acquired for the project.

news.title: Asian Development Bank keen to offer loan for Patna metro rail project
news.para: "The ADB is ready to extend support for the further expansion in metro lines, stations and alignments and they made an offer in the first round meeting with them. If everything goes well, we can plan for the possible expansion of the metro,” the official said.

news.title: Demolish illegal buildings on Musi nalas: NGT committee
news.para: The committee, following its inspection wherein it found several buildings to be unauthorised, also recommended action against officials who permitted such constructions.
